      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A newborn is noted to have a cleft palate, hypocalcemic seizures, and congenital heart defects. On further evaluation, the infant shows significant T-cell deficiency. Which of the following is most characteristic of the infant&#39;s condition, DiGeorge Syndrome?</span></span></span></span></p>",
